      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Electoral Vote: Make It Fair</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tom Neven letter on Michael Lind's Oct 2 Op-Ed on swing states4</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An unmentioned benefit of the system proposed by Michael Lind (Op-Ed, Oct. 2) -- for the states to divide their electoral votes among the candidates on the breakdown of the popular vote -- is that it would render moot the concern over the leaking of election results before the polls close in the West.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An unmentioned benefit of the system proposed by Michael Lind (Op-Ed, Oct. 2) -- for the states to divide their electoral votes among the candidates on the breakdown of the popular vote -- is that it would render moot the concern over the leaking of election results before the polls close in the West.</p>
        <p>If voters in California or Alaska know they can make the decisive difference in a presidential contest, that will reinvigorate the process from Maine to Hawaii.</p>
        <p>TOM NEVEN  Colorado Springs, Oct. 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
